        <h1>LeetCode 1458: Max Dot Product of Two Subsequences (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given two arrays nums1 and nums2, return the maximum dot product between non-empty subsequences of nums1
                and nums2 with the same length. A subsequence of an array is a new array which is formed from the
                original
                array by deleting some (can be none) of the characters without disturbing the relative positions of the
                remaining characters. The dot product of two arrays is the sum of products of corresponding elements.
                The
                solution uses dynamic programming where dp[i][j] represents the maximum dot product using first i
                elements
                of nums1 and first j elements of nums2.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums1 = [2,1,-2,5], nums2 = [3,0,-6] → Output: 18. Take subsequence [2,-2] from nums1 and [3,-6]
                from nums2. Dot product = 2*3 + (-2)*(-6) = 6 + 12 = 18.
                Input: nums1 = [3,-2], nums2 = [2,-6,7] → Output: 21. Take [3] and [7]. Product = 3*7 = 21.
                Input: nums1 = [-1,-1], nums2 = [1,1] → Output: -1. Best is -1*1 = -1.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int maxDotProduct(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; vec1, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; vec2) {
        int n = vec1.size(), m = vec2.size();
        const int NEG_INF = -1e9;
        vector&lt;int&gt; prev(m + 1, NEG_INF);
        for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {
            vector&lt;int&gt; curr(m + 1, NEG_INF);
            for (int j = 1; j &lt;= m; j++) {
                int value = vec1[i - 1] * vec2[j - 1];
                // Either start new subsequence or extend previous
                int pick = (prev[j - 1] == NEG_INF) ? value : max(value, prev[j - 1] + value);
                curr[j] = max({pick, prev[j], curr[j - 1]});
            }
            prev = curr;
        }
        return prev[m];
    }
};</code></pre>
